TypeScript Configuration:
- Use TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- NEVER use `any` or `unknown` types
- All functions must have explicit return types
- All API responses must be typed
- Use proper type inference where appropriate but prefer explicit types for public APIs

Code Style:
- NO inline styles anywhere in the frontend
- NO comments in code
- Use Tailwind CSS classes exclusively for styling
- Use shadcn/ui components for UI elements
- Divide components logically into separate files
- Use "use client" directive ONLY when absolutely required (e.g., hooks, event handlers, browser APIs)

Architecture:
- Follow clean architecture principles
- Modular code organization
- Separation of concerns
- Use Zustand for state management in frontend
- Use React Hook Form with Zod for form validation
- Environment variables for all secrets and configuration

Backend:
- NestJS with proper module structure
- Prisma for database access
- Zod for validation
- Type-safe API responses
- Proper error handling

Frontend:
- Next.js App Router
- Server components by default
- Client components only when necessary
- Type-safe API calls
- Proper error boundaries

Validation:
- Use Zod for all validation schemas
- Validate both frontend and backend inputs
- Type-safe validation results

Database:
- Use Prisma for all database operations
- Type-safe queries
- Proper migrations

AI Integration:
- Mastra AI for structured LLM workflows
- Deterministic JSON-only output
- No markdown or explanations in AI responses
- Structured output schemas

File Uploads:
- Use Multer for file uploads
- Support PDF, DOCX, and image formats
- OCR integration for scanned documents
- Proper error handling for file processing

State Management:
- Zustand for global state
- localStorage for persistence
- Type-safe store actions and state








